                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18201028-135-off730 t18201028-135-victim1292"></join>
                     </persName>
                     
                  , from his person
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18201028-135-person1293">
                  RICHARD 
                  CORNELIUS
               <interp inst="t18201028-135-person1293" type="surname" value="CORNELIUS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18201028-135-person1293" type="given" value="RICHARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18201028-135-person1293" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . On the 25th of September I was in <placeName id="t18201028-135-crimeloc732">Piccadilly</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18201028-135-crimeloc732" type="placeName" value="Piccadilly"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18201028-135-crimeloc732" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18201028-135-off730 t18201028-135-crimeloc732"></join>, near the corner of St. James's-street - a procession was going to the Queen - I was surrounded by a number of persons, and my watch snatched from my pocket. I believe the prisoner to be the man who took it. I saw it in the prisoner's hand, seized him round the body, he was rescued from me, and the prisoner was taken directly.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18201028-135-person1294">
                  FRANCIS 
                  RHIND
               <interp inst="t18201028-135-person1294" type="surname" value="RHIND"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18201028-135-person1294" type="given" value="FRANCIS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18201028-135-person1294" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was with the officers, and saw the prisoner with a gang of twenty or thirty persons surround the prosecutor - I saw him very busy in front of the prosecutor, and laid hold of him; the gang rescued him; I seized him, they kicked and knocked me about. If the officers had not come up I should have been killed.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18201028-135-person1295">
                  EDWARD 
                  RHIND
               <interp inst="t18201028-135-person1295" type="surname" value="RHIND"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18201028-135-person1295" type="given" value="EDWARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18201028-135-person1295" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was there, saw the gang, and heard the prisoner call out stall round - which means, to surround the person - they closed round the prosecutor, he seized the prisoner, I rushed in, and saw the watch-ribbon in his hand.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18201028-135-person1296">
                  CHARLES 
                  READ
               <interp inst="t18201028-135-person1296" type="surname" value="READ"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18201028-135-person1296" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18201028-135-person1296" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I confirm Rhind's statement.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I know nothing of it.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18201028-135-verdict733" type="verdictDescription">
